---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const skills = [
  'Cyber Threat Intelligence',
  'Intrusion Analysis',
  'Detection Engineering',
  'Incident Response',
  'Malware Analysis',
  'Threat Hunting',
  'Intelligence Reporting',
  'Analyst Training',
  'Security Automation',
];

---

<BaseLayout
  title="About VoraSec | Practical Cybersecurity for Individuals & Families"
  description="Learn why VoraSec brings experience from incident response, threat intelligence, malware analysis, and managed detection to personal and home cybersecurity."
>
  <section class="hero shell about-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About VoraSec</p>
    <h1>Serious cybersecurity, made practical for everyday life.</h1>
    <p>
      We bring lessons from real investigations, incident response, and threat
      intelligence to the accounts, identities, and technology people depend on at home.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="shell editorial-stack">
    <section class="editorial-row">
      <div class="editorial-heading">
        <h2>Professional cybersecurity should not be reserved for large organizations.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="editorial-copy">
        <p>
          When something important is at stake, people turn to specialists. They rely on
          knowledgeable professionals to guide a home purchase, support their mental
          health, or protect their physical safety. The digital lives we depend on deserve
          the same focused attention.
        </p>
        <p>
          Large organizations can call on dedicated security teams and specialized
          vendors. Individuals and families are often left with generic checklists,
          automated alerts, and products that may identify a problem without helping them
          solve it.
        </p>
        <p>
          I founded VoraSec to bring focused, professional cybersecurity support to
          individuals and families—not only to organizations with large security budgets.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-row">
      <div class="editorial-heading">
        <p class="eyebrow">Founder</p>
        <h2>About David Hammons</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="editorial-copy">
        <p>
          I’m David Hammons, founder of VoraSec LLC. I’m a U.S. Air Force veteran with
          experience across military intelligence, government, and enterprise
          cybersecurity.
        </p>
        <p>
          During my military service, I provided intelligence support to special operations
          forces in Iraq and Afghanistan. I later worked as an analyst at a government
          agency and investigated and responded to cyberattacks as part of CrowdStrike’s
          managed detection and response team.
        </p>
        <p>
          I hold an M.S. in Cybersecurity and Information Assurance and the GIAC Certified
          Incident Handler—or GCIH—certification. I also hold multiple CompTIA
          certifications focused on cybersecurity defense and penetration testing.
        </p>
        <p>
          That experience matters, but VoraSec is not about bringing enterprise jargon into
          your home. It is about applying professional security judgment to the accounts,
          personal information, devices, and technology you rely on every day.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-row">
      <div class="editorial-heading">
        <h3>Why I do this</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="editorial-copy">
        <p>
          I genuinely enjoy helping people. It is also difficult to see someone lose money,
          access, privacy, or peace of mind to a scam or security problem when the right
          guidance might have reduced the risk or limited the damage.
        </p>
        <p>
          People who have experienced a scam or compromise do not need blame or more fear.
          They need calm, competent help. My goal is to help you understand what matters,
          address the risks that are relevant to you, and establish security habits you can
          realistically maintain.
        </p>
        <p>
          My Christian faith shapes how I approach this work: with honesty, patience,
          respect, and a desire to serve. I welcome clients of every background and belief.
          You will not be judged for what you do not know, overwhelmed with technical
          language, or pressured through fear.
        </p>
        <p>
          I work with families and parents, older adults, busy professionals, people
          responding to scams or suspected compromises, and clients whose public profile,
          occupation, or circumstances create additional digital risk.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-row">
      <div class="editorial-heading">
        <h3>What working with VoraSec looks like</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="editorial-copy">
        <p>
          VoraSec provides on-site personal and home cybersecurity services in San Antonio,
          Texas.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every engagement begins with the most immediate concern. We discuss what happened,
          what prompted you to reach out, and what needs attention first. Then I ask a
          simple question: <strong class="inline-question">How can I help?</strong>
        </p>
        <p>
          You work directly with me. I do not ask you to share your passwords, PINs,
          recovery codes, or other sensitive credentials. When a password needs to be
          entered or changed, you enter it yourself and remain in control of your account.
        </p>
        <p>
          Together, we prioritize what matters most and establish a stronger security
          baseline across your accounts, identity, privacy, devices, and home network.
          Depending on your needs, that may include account and identity protection, scam
          support, personal-exposure reviews, secure home-network deployment, or continuing
          care.
        </p>
        <p>
          The goal is not simply to give you another checklist. It is to make practical
          improvements, help you understand the protections being put in place, and give
          you clear priorities for moving forward. Continuing support is available when
          you need help maintaining or adapting those protections.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-row">
      <div class="editorial-heading">
        <h3>Start with what concerns you most</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="editorial-copy">
        <p>
          You do not need to diagnose the problem or know which service you need before
          contacting VoraSec.
        </p>
        <p>
          Use the contact form to tell me what happened, what concerns you, or what you want
          to protect. I will help you identify an appropriate place to begin.
        </p>
        <p class="security-notice" role="note">
          Please do not include passwords, PINs, recovery codes, Social Security numbers,
          payment-card information, or other sensitive credentials in the contact form.
        </p>
        <div class="buttons">
          <a class="button primary" href="/services#contact">Contact VoraSec</a>
          <a class="button" href="/services">View Services</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <section class="section shell credentials">
    <article>
      <p class="eyebrow">Education</p>
      <h2>Academic foundation.</h2>
      <p><strong>M.S., Cybersecurity and Information Assurance</strong><br />Western Governors University</p>
      <p><strong>B.S., Information Systems Management</strong><br />University of Maryland Global Campus</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <p class="eyebrow">Certifications</p>
      <h2>Technical credentials.</h2>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.credly.com/badges/2e65fde4-fdb2-435c-a142-810d71cb4d31/public_url">
          GIAC Certified Incident Handler (GCIH)
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.credly.com/badges/b7e0e059-fce8-43f9-8fbd-7d5a8098afb5/public_url">
          CompTIA PenTest+ ce
        </a>
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.credly.com/badges/c0e8f766-83ee-4b53-bdec-fffc96cd560a/public_url">
          CompTIA CySA+ ce
        </a>
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section shell expertise">
    <p class="eyebrow">Professional areas</p>
    <ul class="tags">{skills.map((skill) => <li>{skill}</li>)}</ul>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-hero {
    max-width: 880px;
  }

  .editorial-stack {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .editorial-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.75fr) minmax(0, 1.25fr);
    gap: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    align-items: start;
    padding: clamp(3.75rem, 7vw, 5rem) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .editorial-heading h2,
  .editorial-heading h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    max-width: 360px;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 2.9vw, 2.55rem);
  }

  .editorial-copy {
    max-width: 680px;
  }

  .editorial-copy > :first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .editorial-copy > :last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .inline-question {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .security-notice {
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    padding-left: 1rem;
    border-left: 1px solid rgba(245, 167, 167, 0.55);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .credentials {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 5rem;
  }

  .credentials article {
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .credentials strong {
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .credentials a {
    color: var(--text);
    text-underline-offset: 0.2rem;
  }

  .editorial-row a:focus-visible,
  .credentials a:focus-visible {
    outline: 2px solid var(--a);
    outline-offset: 4px;
  }

  .expertise {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

  .expertise .tags {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr));
    gap: 0.75rem 2rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .editorial-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.75rem;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 760px) {
    .credentials {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 3rem;
    }

    .expertise .tags {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (forced-colors: active) {
    .editorial-row .primary {
      color: LinkText;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: LinkText;
    }
  }
</style>
